<p>Those who wish to dine in groups will have to do the following:<br>
<br>
(a) There will be an option to create a unique group name.&nbsp; Please mak=
e sure the members of your group know the group name (for example, if you t=
ype the group name as 'abc1' then make sure your group members know that th=
is is the group name). Whoever creates
 the group name is the leader of the group and the preferences given by tha=
t leader only will be used for allocation. If you are already a leader of a=
 group, you cannot join another group or you cannot come out of the group.<=
/p>
<p>(b) There will be an option for joining a group as member. You will be a=
sked to type the group name that you wish to join.&nbsp; One student can jo=
in in only one group. The members can opt out of the group if they wish; th=
ey can also join another group or register
 as individual at any time before the dead line for registration.<br>
<br>
(c) A group can have a maximum of 8 members only.&nbsp; When the number in =
the group exceeds 8, there will be a flag shown alerting that you cannot jo=
in that group.</p>
<p><br>
(d) Each group will get only one chance in the random pick.<br>
<br>
<br>
Any additional decisions on mess allocation will rest with the Hostel Mess =
Allocation committee. Send you email to:
<a href=3D"mailto:ccw@iitm.ac.in">ccw@iitm.ac.in</a></p>
